                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-08-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular Agent at Aleppo telegraphs the situation of prisoners is unchanged and
                    that the civil authorities have refused to issue traveling <pb facs="1012"
                        n="918" xml:id="pg_918"/> permit for Mrs. Papazian, native American wife of
                    naturalized citizen of the United States, who is professor in Aintab College,
                    and is proceeding with her two children to her home in Massachusetts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
